<@U2670DYLE> <@U0EL0GLEL> <@U243UT96G> Alright, merged.
Frontend and backend got split into two for deploy
To start things up, you'll need to run 2 node instances, setting PORT for the backend:

```cd services
PORT=3000 node app.js```

```cd frontend
API_URL=<http://localhost:3000> node app.js```
or, if you prefer to point to the GAE instance:
```API_URL=<https://services-dot-net-contributor.appspot-preview.com> node app.js```
The current deploy on the server includes commit 7a9d5dba58942b4749a48bbdc23bf1c09f985ecf, but does not yet include any of today's commits from Peter and John.

<!here|@here> We just got done doing a QA pass on the current development branch, and ended up calling it early since there were several issues that need to be addressed. *All* of them appear to be issues that would manifest locally, which mean all of them would have been caught if everyone had done a QA pass on their code before pushing to development. Yes, we QA on the Library rig, but that’s no substitute for doing a once-over locally to ensure changes haven’t introduced regressions.
I’m going to roll the dev deploy back to the last known-good so we don’t have a broken demo on the rig. I need to head home, so that change will hit later tonight.

Also: we’re now in bug-fix/incremental phase. We need to be meticulous about tracking changes to what we delivered as Gold.
To that end: do not make code changes without an associated Jira ticket (even if you need to create one) and do not push a PR without that ticket called out in the commit message.
Thank you --The Management
